cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AVE Database: Agentic Vulnerabilities & Exposures"
message: "If you use this dataset, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Leigh
    given-names: Dillman
    affiliation: "NAIL Institute, Neuravant AI Limited"
repository-code: "https://github.com/NAIL-INSTITUTE-FOR-AGENTIC-SECURITY/ave-database"
url: "https://github.com/NAIL-INSTITUTE-FOR-AGENTIC-SECURITY/ave-database"
abstract: >-
  The AVE Database is the world's first structured catalogue of AI agent
  failure modes — behavioural vulnerabilities, attack vectors, and emergent
  pathologies affecting autonomous AI systems. It contains 36 documented
  vulnerability cards spanning memory poisoning, consensus failures, tool-trust
  exploitation, epistemic contagion, economic denial-of-service, and 
  multi-agent cascade corruption. Each card includes severity rating, 
  reproduction steps, affected models, and defense recommendations.
keywords:
  - agentic AI security
  - vulnerability database
  - LLM safety
  - multi-agent systems
  - AI agent pathology
  - tool-trust exploitation
  - memory poisoning
  - epistemic contagion
